A large white star with twenty-four rays â€” four large rays at the cardinal points and twenty smaller rays â€” is situated in the upper hoist-side corner above the diagonal bands.

flags.alt: The flag of Panama is composed of four equal rectangular areas â€” a white rectangular area with a blue five-pointed star at its center, a red rectangular area, a white rectangular area with a red five-pointed star at its center, and a blue rectangular area â€” in the upper hoist side, upper fly side, lower fly side and lower hoist side respectively.
The flag of Micronesia has a light blue field, at the center of which are four five-pointed white stars arranged in the shape of a diamond.

The flag of Timor-Leste has a red field with two isosceles triangles which share a common base on the hoist end. The smaller black triangle, which bears a five-pointed white star at its center and spans one-third the width of the field, is superimposed on the larger yellow triangle that extends to the center of the field.

flags.alt: The flag of Ecuador is composed of the horizontal bands of yellow, blue and red, with the yellow band twice the height of the other two bands. The Ecuadorian coat of arms is superimposed in the center of the field.
The flag of Cambodia features three horizontal bands of blue, red and blue, with a white depiction of the temple complex, Angkor Wat centered in the red band.
The flag of Palau has a light blue field with a large golden-yellow circle that is offset slightly towards the hoist side of center.
